        <content><![CDATA[    <h1 class="title topictitle1">Create the MID Server user</h1>        <div class="body taskbody">        <div class="section context"><span class="ph">The MID Server connects to an instance by using the SOAP web                service. To allow authentication with the instance, create a separate user account                for each MID Server or share the same account across multiple MID Servers. Grant                each MID Server user the mid_server role, which is required for the MID Server user                on any instance on which basic authentication is enabled. The mid_server role allows                the MID Server to access protected tables when strict SOAP security is in place. The                system adds the necessary SOAP roles automatically with this role.</span></div>        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step stepexpand">                <span class="ph cmd">Complete the fields in the form.</span>            </li><li class="li step stepexpand">                <span class="ph cmd">Click <span class="ph uicontrol">Submit</span></span>                <div class="itemgroup info">The system automatically adds the mid_server role to this user. </div>            </li></ol>    </div>    <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:SetUpMIDRole&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Set up the MID Server user and role</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
